            "body": "@davidism I sorta don't want to submit a PR inasmuch as it's almost no work to make the required change, but it requires knowledge of Flask I don't actually have. I'd basically be repeating what you told me & assuming it's correct (and maybe you're just fucking with me for the lulz), but also speaking _ex cathedra_ to the Flask n00bs of the world, who deserve to have their docs written by somebody who knows what he's talking about (to the extent that they deserve anything with a free project, but still). It doesn't strike me as a very sensible way to run a project.\r\n\r\nBut supposing I was going to make a PR: what is the operational definition of \"just doing development?\" And am I correct in thinking that flask is in development mode both when running on the builtin server with debug=False _and_ when running on (say) uwsgi with debug=True?"
